climbs.name: Public Enemy Direct AKA Public Enemy Number 1

content.description: Start as for Public Enemy and instead of heading left after the foot cut wrestle your way up the Dihedral.  Physical!
content.location: From the Cabin Parking on the west bluff south this boulder is just above the last cabin about 50 feet off the trail.  The roof faces the trail.

content.description: A cool roof 100 feet off of the trail just above the last cabin before the trail starts on the south side of the West Bluff.
content.location: Start left hand in the horizontal crack at the base of the roof and a slippery sloper near the right arete.  Climb out the roof and trend left towards the end.  There is a jug at the end and mantel out onto the ledge.

climbs.name: Notorious
climbs.fa: Ian CB, Dalton, Cashman and Duffy

content.description: An aesthetic line, though a bit dabby, with interesting movement and easy access…Start sitting with underclings in the pit.  Climb through edges and gastons, rocking over the feet.  A few more moves and a nice finish with large holds follows.
content.protection: Several pads and likely a blubber or a sweat shirt or two.
content.location: Hidden on the south side of the Public Enemy boulder.  Just above the cabins.

content.description: Start sitting with two large underclings, slot the left kneebar and climb up face using sloping sidepulls and nice two finger pocket, topout left rolling up onto the horn.
content.location: On the next boulder uphill from public enemy 15ft uphill just past the large tree.

content.description: Sit start, climb up arete.  Rock is a touch fractured and chossy down low.
content.location: Arete to right of Public Enemy by 5 feet.  Directly above northernmost cabin by 50 feet.

content.description: Start as for public enemy, and somehow climb up the vert face to the right.  Funky moves, public enemy # 3?  Pretty interesting climbing really.
A buttress of rock that beckons you up from the Tumbled Rocks trail and into the woods.  This is the simplest starting point for finding all the formations in this zone.
